The paper discusses a security concern in deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Security and Privacy) category. The proposed framework uses optimization techniques to modify the DNN parameters, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The modification aims to misclassify input images, which is a task related to computer vision, and hence, it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance analysis of the proposed framework, which could be related to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
